platform, topic and product.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Project Sharing Platforms</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://inventhub.io/\">InventHub</a> - Git-based project hosting and collaboration platform for hardware development.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.hackster.io/news\">Hackster.io</a> - Another blog covering electronics.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Forums</h2><h3>Help</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/AskElectronics/\">/r/askelectronics</a> - Sub-reddit dedicated to help on electronics topics.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Forums</h2><h3>Help</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://electronics.stackexchange.com\">Electronics Stack Exchange</a> - Question and answer site for electronics running on the popular Stack Overflow service.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Forums</h2><h3>Help</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.eevblog.com/forum/beginners/\">EEVBlog beginners forum</a> - Good place for beginner questions, other sub-forums on EEVblog should be suitable for questions on more advanced topics.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://theamphour.com/\">The Amp Hour</a> - Off-the-cuff chat about electronics with Chris Gammel and Dave Jones (EEVBlog), often with guests</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://macrofab.com/blog/podcast/\">MacroFab Engineering Podcast</a> - Weekly podcast where Parker and Stephen from MacroFab discuss EE topics and industry news.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Podcasts</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://theengineeringcommons.com/\">The Engineering Commons Podcast</a> - Covers general engineering topics from mechanical to electrical.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>3D Part Models</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://grabcad.com/library/electronic-components-1\">GrabCad</a> - Community supported database of 3D models with a large number of electronic component models.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>3D Part Models</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.3dcontentcentral.com\">3D ContentCentral</a> - Website dedicated to 3D models of parts (requires login).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/PwnKitteh/InsanelyCheapElectronics\">PwnKitteh/InsanelyCheapElectronics</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/PwnKitteh/InsanelyCheapElectronics\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">210</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":210,\"repo\":\"PwnKitteh/InsanelyCheapElectronics\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A list of cheap electronics from China, that you can use in your projects.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/intajay/open-electronics\">intajay/open-electronics</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/intajay/open-electronics\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"c