, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">115</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":115,\"repo\":\"cajt/list_of_robot_electronics\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A GitHub list of resources, projects and products for robot electronics.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/embedded-boston/awesome-embedded-systems\">embedded-boston/awesome-embedded-systems</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/embedded-boston/awesome-embedded-systems\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">467</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":467,\"repo\":\"embedded-boston/awesome-embedded-systems\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Awesome list of embedded programming resources.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://tcad.com/Software.html\">TCAD Central</a> - List of Technology CAD (TCAD) software and resources from the maker of DEVSIM.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-18T04:34:50.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/matarofe\">Robert Feranec</a> - 100+ Hardware design tips and tricks. Videos about Schematic design and PCB layout.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-12T03:32:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2><h3>University Course Archives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://inst.eecs.berkeley.edu/classes-eecs.html\">Berkeley EECS</a> - Comprehensive EE &#x26; CS course website archives.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2><h3>University Course Archives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://cmosedu.com\">Dr. Jacob Baker</a> - Courses and tutorials, professor at The University of Nevada, Las Vegas.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2><h3>University Course Archives</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cerc.utexas.edu/~jaa/teaching.html\">Dr. Abraham</a>, <a href=\"http://users.ece.utexas.edu/~mcdermot/\">Dr. McDermot</a>, and <a href=\"http://users.ece.utexas.edu/~valvano/\">Dr. Valvano</a> - Courses materials, professors at UT Austin</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.analog.com/en/design-center/design-tools-and-calculators/ltspice-simulator.html\">LTspice</a> - The industry standard free SPICE circuit simulator from Linear Technologies. Also see the unofficial <a href=\"http://ltwiki.org/?title=Main_Page\">LTwiki</a> and <a href=\"https://groups.io/g/LTspice\">Group</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://qucs.sourceforge.net/\">Qucs</a> - Open source, cross-platform, non-SPICE-based circuit simulator, with with S-parameter and Harmonic Balance capability.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://opencircuitdesign.com\">Open Circuit Design Software</a> - Open Source, full EDA suite chip design suite, focused on keeping up with commercial tools.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.ti.com/tool/TINA-TI\">TINA-TI</a> - Exclusive <a href=\"https://www.tina.com\">DesignSoft-TINA</a> build for Texas Instruments, bundled with Texas Instruments Models.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cppsim.com/\">CppSim</a> - Free, open source circuit simulator that leverages the C++ language to achieve very fast simulation times.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.scilab.org/\">Scilab with Xcos</a> - Free, open source numerical computing alternative to MATLAB. Xcos provides Electrical System modeling capability similar to Simulink.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Verilog HDL Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.veripool.org/wiki/verilator\">Verilator</a> - Free, open source Verilog compiler. Test benches are in C++ or SystemC. Very fast, but limted to 2-state, cycle-based simulation, and synthesizeable code only.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Verilog HDL Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://iverilog.icarus.com/\">Icarus Verilog</a> - Free, open source verilog interpreter. Test benches are in behavioral verilog. Simulation is 4-state, and event-based.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-11T16:35:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2><h3>Technical Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.instructables.com/id/Uses-of-Different-Soldering-Iron-Tips/\">Uses of Different Soldering Iron Tips</a> - Covers what all those different soldering iron tips are good for.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Gerber Viewers</h2><h3>Online</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://tracespace.io/\">Tracespace Viewer</a> -  Gerber viewer that lets you inspect the individual layers as well as the board preview.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Gerber Viewers</h2><h3>Online</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.gerblook.org/\">Gerblook</a> - Online Gerber viewer powered by Gerbv.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Gerber Viewers</h2><h3>Online</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://stackrate.de/viewer/\">Stackrate Viewer</a> - Easy to use online gerber viewer with trace hovering and measurement tools.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free EDA Packages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://kicad-pcb.org/\">KiCad</a> - Open source EDA package with push and shove router, differential pairs and much more.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>CAD Specific</h2><h3>KiCad</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://silica.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/kicad-cheatsheet.pdf\">Cheatsheet</a> (also <a href=\"https://silica.io/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/kicad-cheatsheet-landscape.pdf\">in landscape</a>) - Short PDF that goes over the menus and keyboard shortcuts for the most common operations.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>CAD Specific</h2><h3>Eagle</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.element14.com/community/community/eagle/blog/2015/01/19/eagle-ulps-every-user-should-know\">List of ULPs everyone should know</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Inventory Management and Purchasing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://kitspace.org/1-click-bom/\">1-click BOM</a> - Browser extensions that automates purchasing and part searching.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Other Lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.eevblog.com/forum/eda/pcbeda-software-list/\">PCB/EDA software list on the EEVblog forums</a> - A much more comprehensive list of all the software tools available.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-08T03:12:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.spectrum-soft.com/download/download.shtm\">Micro-Cap</a> - Professional-grade mixed signal simulator with wide variety of interactive simulation types.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-10T16:50:01.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>PCB Syntax Highlighting</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Alhadis/language-pcb\">Language PCB</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Alhadis/language-pcb\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":12,\"repo\":\"Alhadis/language-pcb\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Syntax highlighting for various PCB formats.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-27T14:52:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free EDA Packages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.autodesk.com/products/eagle/overview\">Eagle</a> - One of the most popular EDA packages due to it's (board size restricted) free version.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-28T12:49:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>CAD Specific</h2><h3>KiCad</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/openscopeproject/InteractiveHtmlBom\">InteractiveHtmlBom</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/openscopeproject/InteractiveHtmlBom\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1534,\"repo\":\"openscopeproject/InteractiveHtmlBom\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A html BOM generation tool for manual pick and place.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-28T12:14:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://dangerousprototypes.com/blog/\">Dangerous Prototypes</a> - Blog about open source hardware projects and interesting app notes.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-28T12:10:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>PCB Batching Services</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jlcpcb.com/\">JLCPCB</a> - Low cost PCB batching service with inhouse low cost SMT service.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-28T12:06:49.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free EDA Packages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/horizon-eda/horizon\">Horizon EDA</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/horizon-eda/horizon\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">632</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":632,\"repo\":\"horizon-eda/horizon\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A free and open source EDA tool with the focus on shortcut operation.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-09-28T12:05:16.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free EDA Packages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://librepcb.org/\">LibrePCB</a> - A new, powerful and intuitive EDA tool for everyone, cross-platform and GNU GPLv3.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-21T16:25:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2><h3>Technical Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://learn.sparkfun.com/tutorials/tags/skill\">\"skill\" tag on learn.sparkfun.com</a> - A wide variety of technical tutorials on various EE related skills.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-18T13:12:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning</h2><h3>Technical Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mightyohm.com/blog/2011/04/soldering-is-easy-comic-book/\">Soldering is Easy</a> - Comic book that goes over the basics of soldering that has been translated into quite a few languages.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-08-18T13:12:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>CAD Specific</h2><h3>KiCad</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://contextualelectronics.com/courses/shine-on-you-crazy-kicad/\">Contextual Electronics' Shine on You Crazy KiCad</a> - Beginner video tutorial that gets you to a manufactured board as quickly as possible.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T23:43:08.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>CAD Specific</h2><h3>KiCad</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLy2022BX6Eso532xqrUxDT1u2p4VVsg-q\">Contextual Electronics' Getting to Blinky Tutorial</a> - A more comprehensive beginner to intermediate video tutorial.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T23:43:08.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development Board Retailers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/\">Adafruit</a> - Another retailer and designer with excellent selection and tutorials.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T23:43:08.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/EEVblog\">EEVblog</a> - One of the earliest and most successful YouTube channels where Dave Jones does teardowns, tutorials and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T23:43:08.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free EDA Packages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://diptrace.com\">DipTrace</a> - Quality Schematic Capture and PCB Design software with (pin and signal layer restricted) free version.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:05:49.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Subscription Kit Services</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.adafruit.com/adabox/\">AdaBox</a> - Curated Adafruit products, unique collectibles, and exclusive discounts. All delivered quarterly.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:05:33.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Gerber Viewers</h2><h3>Online</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://circuitpeople.com\">CircuitPeople</a> - No frills 2D layer viewer for Gerbers, without the excessive processing.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:04:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>PCB Batching Services</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://dirtypcbs.com/store/pcbs\">Dirty PCBs</a> - Low cost PCB batching service that prides itself on its \"dirty\" quality.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:04:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Part Search Engines</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.findchips.com/\">Findchips</a> - Part search from Supply Frame.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:04:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development Board Retailers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.sparkfun.com/\">Sparkfun</a> - Retailer and designer of open source electronics development boards and other equipment and materials with excellent accompanying tutorials.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:04:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Forums</h2><h3>Discussion</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.eevblog.com/forum/\">EEVBlog forum</a> - Probably the largest and most active forum to discuss electronic engineering topics.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:04:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Forums</h2><h3>Discussion</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/electronics/\">/r/electronics</a> and <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/ECE/\">/r/ECE</a> are the two most active sub-reddits for EE topics.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-04-28T02:04:20.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Simulators</h2><h3>Analog and Mixed Signal Circuit Simulators</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://icircuitapp.com/\">iCircuit</a> - Easy to use electronic circuit simulator, its advanced simulation engine can handle both analog and digital circuits and features realtime always-on analysis.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-03-03T14:24:26.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Inventory Management and Purchasing</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Part-DB/Part-DB\">Part-DB</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Part-DB/Part-DB\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">115</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":115,\"repo\":\"Part-DB/Part-DB\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Another open source web service for managing part inventory with a permission system and a good barcode generator.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-02-07T22:08:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>PCB Batching Services</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://aisler.net\">Aisler</a> - Affordable quality circuit boards made in and shipped from Europe (Germany).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-13T11:32:35.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hackaday.com\">Hackaday</a> - Probably the most popular blog covering electronics and hardware hacking with a whole staff of writers.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-31T10:50:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.baldengineer.com\">Bald Engineer</a> - Project logs, tutorials and articles about electronics and embedded software by James Lewis.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-31T10:50:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://rheingoldheavy.com\">Rheingold Heavy</a> - More project logs, tutorials and articles about electronics and embedded software, these ones by Dan Hienzsch.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-31T10:50:39.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLowKtXNTBypGqImE405J2565dvjafglHU\">Ben Eater</a> - Series of videos on building an 8-bit computer on breadboards with excellent explanations of all the sub-circuits.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-03-07T17:22:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development Board Retailers</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.tindie.com\">Tindie</a> - Marketplace for electronics makers to sell low volume batches of their own designs.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-02-10T16:17:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Part Search Engines</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://octopart.com\">Octopart</a> - Probably the most well known part search engine.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-02-10T16:10:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Part Search Engines</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://parts.io/\">Parts.io</a> - Another search engine from Supply Frame geared towards discovering new parts.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-02-10T16:10:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Project Sharing Platforms</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hackaday.io\">Hackaday.io</a> - Social site for sharing projects from the popular blog.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-02-06T12:48:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTM